# DIGIfor1Health Jekyll Project

This is a Jekyll static site using the Type-on-Strap theme.

## Project Structure

- **`_config.yml`**: Main Jekyll configuration
- **`_includes/`**: Reusable Liquid templates (navbar, footer, etc.)
- **`_layouts/`**: Page layout templates
- **`_sass/`**: SCSS stylesheets (customize via `_sass/includes/` and `_sass/_custom.scss`)
- **`pages/`**: Markdown pages (about.md, contact.md, etc.)
- **`_posts/`**: Blog posts
- **`assets/`**: Static assets (images, JS, CSS)

## Key Conventions

- **Liquid templates**: Use `.liquid` extension for includes and layouts
- **Styling**: Customize via `_sass/includes/_navbar.scss`, `_sass/_custom.scss`
- **Pages**: Create in `pages/` directory as `.md` files
- **Images**: Store in `assets/img/` or page-specific `assets/img/` folders
- **Multi-language**: Site supports Swedish (default) and English (`en/` directory)

## Common Tasks

- **Navbar changes**: Edit `_includes/default/navbar.liquid` and `_sass/includes/_navbar.scss`
- **Footer changes**: Edit `_includes/default/footer.liquid` and `_sass/includes/_footer.scss`
- **Page content**: Edit files in `pages/` directory
- **Styling**: Modify SCSS files in `_sass/` directory

## Build & Deploy

- Uses Jekyll (Ruby-based)
- Check `Gemfile` for dependencies
- GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`
